<div id="review_189876220" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/189876220" />
    <a title="Sheila Hollinghead" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/5252004-sheila-hollinghead"><img alt="Sheila Hollinghead" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1442616001p2/5252004.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/189876220?book_show_action=true">Jul 26, 2011</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Sheila Hollinghead" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Sheila Hollinghead" href="/user/show/5252004-sheila-hollinghead">Sheila Hollinghead</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer189876220" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6234392964836051937">I&apos;m a huge Agatha Christie fan, but I felt this book was a waste of my time and money. I did learn a little about Christie&apos;s writing habits--she had terrible handwriting most of her life (ironically getting better as she aged. What&apos;s up with that?), made lists of scenes and rearranged them to suit herself, and often did not know who the murderer would be when she began to plot the book. Interesting tidbits but not worth trudging through the book to learn such trivia. The two short stories were a</span>
  <span id="freeText6234392964836051937" style="display:none">I'm a huge Agatha Christie fan, but I felt this book was a waste of my time and money. I did learn a little about Christie's writing habits--she had terrible handwriting most of her life (ironically getting better as she aged. What's up with that?), made lists of scenes and rearranged them to suit herself, and often did not know who the murderer would be when she began to plot the book. Interesting tidbits but not worth trudging through the book to learn such trivia. The two short stories were actually variations of published stories. One was mildly interesting as it was based on Hitler and had him renouncing Nazism and finding God. Otherwise, not much else to recommend it. Sadly disappointed. </span>
  <a data-text-id="6234392964836051937" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


