  <span id="freeText9349967339420042050" style="display:none">Enjoyed getting a little into the mind of Agatha Christie. This book deciphers her numerous notebooks where she jotted down her ideas for plot points, scenes and characters, etc. Rating it was difficult as it's more for Christieophiles than average readers and I admit to skimming much of it; however, it was fun to glimpse some of her thought processes. I've always admired her work yet was blown away with her amazing output and longevity at the top of her game. How she did it remains a great mystery!</span>
