        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2764762340" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17480669503578426141">If you are hoping for some insight into Christie&apos;s genius you won&apos;t find it in this book sadly as her thought processes were not directly committed to the notebooks. The author does his best to decipher Christie&apos;s sprawling handwriting of course. Some of her solutions are necessarily revealed so care is needed so as not to spoil any unread stories. This led to me skipping pages here and there but I know too that you can read a Christie a month for years and then start again, safe in the knowledg</span>
  <span id="freeText17480669503578426141" style="display:none">If you are hoping for some insight into Christie's genius you won't find it in this book sadly as her thought processes were not directly committed to the notebooks. The author does his best to decipher Christie's sprawling handwriting of course. Some of her solutions are necessarily revealed so care is needed so as not to spoil any unread stories. This led to me skipping pages here and there but I know too that you can read a Christie a month for years and then start again, safe in the knowledge that you will have forgotten the solution in most cases. </span>
  <a data-text-id="17480669503578426141" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
