    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_3163296165" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3163296165" />
    <a title="Rita" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/960472-rita"><img alt="Rita" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1339173348p2/960472.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3163296165?book_show_action=true">Jan 27, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Rita" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Rita" href="/user/show/960472-rita">Rita</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3163296165" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10065691924417320842">I was so tempted by this book but found the detail and jumping around among the notebooks to show how her stories came to fruition to be extremely confusing and then downright boring. Agatha Christie&apos;s ability to tell her stories is amazing and I have been reading them for over 40 years. <br/><br/>I can only assume that trying to describe how her mind works to bring all her stories to life was the purpose of this book. To me, it is a lovely guide to the notebooks if you can actually see the notebooks and </span>
  <span id="freeText10065691924417320842" style="display:none">I was so tempted by this book but found the detail and jumping around among the notebooks to show how her stories came to fruition to be extremely confusing and then downright boring. Agatha Christie's ability to tell her stories is amazing and I have been reading them for over 40 years. <br /><br />I can only assume that trying to describe how her mind works to bring all her stories to life was the purpose of this book. To me, it is a lovely guide to the notebooks if you can actually see the notebooks and peruse them as the author describes his findings.</span>
  <a data-text-id="10065691924417320842" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

