<div id="review_2322565973" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2322565973" />
    <a title="AdiTurbo" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/2199883-aditurbo"><img alt="AdiTurbo" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1267856658p2/2199883.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2322565973?book_show_action=true">Mar 09, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="AdiTurbo" class="user" itemprop="url" name="AdiTurbo" href="/user/show/2199883-aditurbo">AdiTurbo</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2322565973" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9371404631555212242">DNF. I hoped this book would actually provide Christie&apos;s diaries. Instead, we get very tiny pieces of them here and there, and a lot of trivial information about her writing methods, habits and even her handwriting. I was looking forward to learn more about her personality and unique mind, but found myself drowning in details Curran deemed interesting, but often aren&apos;t. On the way he manages to spoil almost all of Christie&apos;s novels and plays. Not what I planned to read.</span>
  <span id="freeText9371404631555212242" style="display:none">DNF. I hoped this book would actually provide Christie's diaries. Instead, we get very tiny pieces of them here and there, and a lot of trivial information about her writing methods, habits and even her handwriting. I was looking forward to learn more about her personality and unique mind, but found myself drowning in details Curran deemed interesting, but often aren't. On the way he manages to spoil almost all of Christie's novels and plays. Not what I planned to read.</span>
  <a data-text-id="9371404631555212242" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


