    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_4155382740" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4155382740" />
    <a title="Robert May" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/57442417-robert-may"><img alt="Robert May" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1467859532p2/57442417.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4155382740?book_show_action=true">Aug 04, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Robert May" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Robert May" href="/user/show/57442417-robert-may">Robert May</a>
      </span>

          added it




        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4155382740" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16907663416684150934">Unless you are an academic, and even then, this book is a major waste of time. The &quot;new&quot; stories are short drafts of stories she later developed into better novels. I learned Agatha&apos;s handwriting was impossible to read, that she was very unorganized and that she worked out multiple endings for many of her mysteries. None of this improved my appreciation or knowledge of her work. Sorry, Mr. Curran, I appreciate your effort, but it was all naught for very much.</span>
  <span id="freeText16907663416684150934" style="display:none">Unless you are an academic, and even then, this book is a major waste of time. The "new" stories are short drafts of stories she later developed into better novels. I learned Agatha's handwriting was impossible to read, that she was very unorganized and that she worked out multiple endings for many of her mysteries. None of this improved my appreciation or knowledge of her work. Sorry, Mr. Curran, I appreciate your effort, but it was all naught for very much.</span>
  <a data-text-id="16907663416684150934" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


